INSTANCE.ATTRIBUTE:
This process describes the main directives for planning the necessary capacity of vehicles. This process is also valid for countries where R&S activity is outsourced.

Planning of necessary transportation capacity covers:
?    Calculation of annual transportation capacity needs, based on yearly sales forecast figures, according to Business Model (as defined by LOG_1_G3_LOG1 Contract management at Logistics – Road transportation GOR), i.e. by fuel types, regions, road tanker types’ specific requirements (e.g. pump, rigid tank-cars, etc.), considering also seasonality if applicable;
?    Cooperation with the local organisational unit in charge of transportation contract management, in order to support its Demand Management & Contracting function;
?    Short-term (monthly, weekly, daily) planning of necessary transportation capacity.
